<subSubSection id="C322B8883A29FFB0FF0AEA76FF42F9EF" pageId="41" pageNumber="1174" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B87EB033A29FFB0FF0AEA76FF42F9EF" blockId="41.[178,1085,1334,1591]" pageId="41" pageNumber="1174">
Comment: The original description of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3890803A29FFB0FDCBEA77FC9DFA93" authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1907" box="[627,811,1334,1355]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Medon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="1174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subopacus">
<emphasis id="B94C37113A29FFB0FDCBEA77FC9DFA93" box="[627,811,1334,1355]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="1174">Medon subopacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is based on an unspecified number of 
<typeStatus id="548355A13A29FFB0FE92EA15FE35FAB1" box="[298,387,1364,1385]" pageId="41" pageNumber="1174">syntypes</typeStatus>
from &quot;Kanagawa, Bukenji, Kuenji. Unter faulenden Schilfhaufen mehrfach gesammelt&quot; (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA996F23A29FFB0FE1CEA30FDD7FA5F" author="BERNHAUER M" box="[420,609,1393,1415]" pageId="41" pageNumber="1174" pagination="371 - 414" refId="ref27629" refString="BERNHAUER M. (1907): Zur Staphylinidenfauna von Japan. - Verhandlungen der Kaiserlich- Koniglichen Zoologisch-Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien 57: 371 - 414." type="journal article" year="1907">BERNHAUER 1907</bibRefCitation>
). Five 
<typeStatus id="548355A13A29FFB0FD15EA30FCB0FA5E" box="[685,774,1393,1414]" pageId="41" pageNumber="1174">syntypes</typeStatus>
from Kanagawa and Bukenji were located in the Bernhauer collection and in the collections of the BMNH. The male from Kanagawa is designated as the 
<typeStatus id="548355A13A29FFB0FDFAEAEAFD14FA19" box="[578,674,1451,1473]" pageId="41" pageNumber="1174">lectotype</typeStatus>
. SCHÜLKE &amp; SMETANA (2015) list the species in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3890803A29FFB0FE9DEA88FE2FFA06" authorityName="DEJEAN" authorityYear="1833" box="[293,409,1481,1502]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lithocharis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="1174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94C37113A29FFB0FE9DEA88FE2FFA06" box="[293,409,1481,1502]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="1174">Lithocharis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. An examination of the above type material revealed that it is conspecific with 
<taxonomicName id="4C3890803A29FFB0FED8EAA6FCADFA24" authority="(SHARP, 1874)" baseAuthorityName="Sharp" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[352,795,1510,1532]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Panscopaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="1174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lithocharoides">
<emphasis id="B94C37113A29FFB0FED8EAA6FDC8FA23" box="[352,638,1510,1532]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="1174">Panscopaeus lithocharoides</emphasis>
(SHARP, 1874)
</taxonomicName>
, a species widespread in the East Palaearctic region, from the Himalaya across 
<collectingCountry id="F32FAB933A29FFB0FD68E942FCBAF9C1" box="[720,780,1539,1561]" name="China" pageId="41" pageNumber="1174">China</collectingCountry>
eastwards to 
